Chapter-1

variables in JS
-----------------
 variables are containers for data
 data can be changed	
 Dynamically typed (can be changed the value any time)
  
a=b 
= assignment operator

variable rules----
1.variable names are case sentitive "a" "A" is different
2. only letters,digits,underscore,and $ is allowed (not even spaces)
3. only a letter,underscore ,$ should be 1st character
4. reserved words cannot be variable names

let,const,var-----

var: variables can be redeclared. A global scope variable 

let: variables cannot be redeclared but can be updated. A block scope variable

const: variable cannot be redeclared or updated. A block{} scope variable

------------------------------------------------------------------
Data Types in JS

Primitive datatypes----
Number, String, Boolean, Undefined, Null, BigInt, Symbol

non primitives----
objects(arrays,functions)

objects-collection of values
students(name,age,marks,isPass)
key:value
obj.key
obj["key"]

let -> can change
const -> cannot change
const obj -> key (can change)

