Chapter-2

Operators & Conditional Statements
--------------------------------------

comments in js
--part of code which is not executed

// single line comment
/* multi line comment */


operators in JS
---------------
used to perform some operation on data

1.Arithmetic operators
+,-,*,/

2.Modulus operator
%  -remainder

3.Exponentiation
**  power 

4.increment(unary operator)
++   a=a+1    ,,,,  a++  (post) , ++a  (pre)

5.decrement(unary)
--   a=a-1

6.Assignment operators
= += -= *= %= **=

= assign
+= a=a+1  

7.Comparison operators
>,<,<=,>=

== equal to
!= not equal
=== equal to &type  (strict version)
!== not equal to & type

8.Logical operator
&&- and       true true =true
||- or        false false= false
! - not       true->false  ,, false->true



conditional statements
------------------------

if statement

if else

else if


Ternary operators
-------------------

condition ? true output : false output

